(CNN) Bahrain has revoked the nationality of 138 people convicted of terrorism in a mass trial, according to the kingdom's state news agency.
The Bahrain News Agency citing Advocate General Ahmed al-Hammadi reported Tuesday that the High Criminal Court also sentenced 69 terror suspects to life in prison.
Thirty-nine of the defendants received sentences up to 10 years, while 23 received 7-year terms.
The defendants were accused of attempting to form a terror group in the country backed by Iran's elite Revolutionary Guards , according to BNA.
The alleged group was "tasked to target" the country's oil installations and "vital locations in order to destabilize Bahrain," reported the state agency.